subject: (good and bad points) Stack Exchange
text:
Hi all, this is my first contribution to the project. I'm having a look at Stack Exchange's Terms of Service (http://stackexchange.com/legal - quite accessible from the footer) and I found some interesting and well explained points. I'm not sure if I should start a thread for each of these, so here are the "highlights" (the number between parenthesis is the article in the ToS). Count me in for any further research!

(1)
Good: No third parties 
Bad: SE may change, suspend or discontinue the Services at any time
Good: If terms change, they notify

(2)
Good?: Copyright as collective work or compilation

(3)
Neutral?: All subscriber's content is perpetually and irrevocably licensed to Stack Exchange under the Creative Commons Attribution Share Alike (I like the CC, I don't like the sound of 'perpetually and irrevocably' though!)

(7)
Good: Doesn't require real name

(10)
Good: If there are fees and they change, you will be notified

(11)
Good: Can be terminated by user any time (and by them if you breach the services)

--
